abstract: TUSCUMBIA, Ala., Sept. 1--President Carter, opening his re-election campaign in an industrial and farming region of his native South, denounced the Ku Klux Klan at a Labor Day rally this afternoon and declared that the United States had been "inspired and gratified" by the gains made by workers this weekend in Poland.
